verbose_text: In most previously reported cases, patients were known with conditions associated with increased risk of ventricular tachyarrhythmia such as dilated cardiomyopathy,5, 6 prior myocardial infarction with left ventricular ejection fraction of 30%,7 significant general atherosclerosis with previous history of stroke8 or hypercalcemia combined with severely decreased level of potassium.5, 9 Both monomorphic VT5, 10 and polymorphic VT/VF have been described8, 9 with severe PHPT.
